
## Sico Protospatharios

Sico (Italian: Sicone) (died 1054) was a Byzantine protospatharios leading troops in Italy from about 1052. He had a Lombard name, though he was a Greek official. He was an official under Argyrus.
Sico was killed in battle outside the walls of Matera fighting the Normans of Humphrey of Hauteville.

